00:00:00.384 --> 00:00:04.032
<b>It is common for people to bend forward at the waist </b>
<b>when reaching down to lift. </b>

00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:10.816
<b>In Safety In Motion, we know it’s better to lower our body </b>
<b>by flexing our knees like this:</b>

00:00:10.848 --> 00:00:14.816
<b>Can you see the difference between these two very different motions?</b>

00:00:16.192 --> 00:00:20.036
<b>One reason it’s tempting to bend at the waist, </b>
<b>as opposed to flexing our knees</b>

00:00:20.037 --> 00:00:24.695
<b>is our limitations in strength and flexibility </b>
<b>of our legs and hips.</b>

00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:30.144
<b>The Step and Flex Re-energizer is a great way </b>
<b>to not only warm up our core and leg muscles</b>

00:00:30.208 --> 00:00:33.280
<b>but also to train our bodies to lift with better physical technique.</b>

